800400aa-4853-4805-9b7e-8e1cb533d7a9.09a8ec00-4ef0-462f-a5d4-329a3f515eb8.description=
Deletes a registry key

Inputs\:
host - hostname or ip address
key - The key to create. For Example\: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Services\Browser
recursive - true or false, whether to recursively delete child keys.
username - user to connect to host as
password - password to connect to host as

Responses\:
success - registry key deleted
failure - something went wrong

Returns\:
The raw XML response. Note, the format of this changes depending on the type of the key.

800400aa-4853-4805-9b7e-8e1cb533d7a9.78aaf547-7f94-4cda-b0f0-4385fe570811.prompt=Enter a value for host 800400aa-4853-4805-9b7e-8e1cb533d7a9.794321f4-338a-47f0-81f4-6bc3974cb468.description=
Reads a value from a registry key

Inputs\:
host - hostname or ip address
key - The key to read from. For Example\: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Services\Browser
valueName - the name of the value in the key to read.
username - user to connect to host as
password - password to connect to host as

Responses\:
success - value read
failure - something went wrong

Returns\:
The raw XML response. Note, the format of this changes depending on the type of the key.

Extra Results\:
type - The type of the registry key.
value - the value of the registry key. If the type is REG_BINARY or REG_MULTI_SZ it will return a newline delimited list containing the elements of the array stored in the registry.

NOTE\: Some environment variables may be filled in by the registry api when reading keys. Be careful when modifying.
800400aa-4853-4805-9b7e-8e1cb533d7a9.7cfd4361-703a-489a-9991-2a571a756a2c.prompt=Enter a value for key 800400aa-4853-4805-9b7e-8e1cb533d7a9.8c3cb4ea-ce72-4e5f-bc42-1be8f63eb684.prompt=Enter a value for host 800400aa-4853-4805-9b7e-8e1cb533d7a9.8cacce95-c034-4e8e-84ca-bdea028f0031.prompt=Enter a value for key 800400aa-4853-4805-9b7e-8e1cb533d7a9.90d709c8-b9a4-4fca-a793-8b9ca618b06c.description=
Modifies a value in a registry key

Inputs\:
host - hostname or ip address
key - The key to create. For Example\: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Services\Browser
valueName - the name of the value to modify.
value - the new value to store in valueName.
type - the type to store value as.
username - user to connect to host as
password - password to connect to host as

Responses\:
success - registry key value was changed
failure - something went wrong

Returns\:
The raw XML response. Note, the format of this changes depending on the type of the key.

Responses\:

Returns\:
The raw XML response.

800400aa-4853-4805-9b7e-8e1cb533d7a9.dda52e00-caed-4e99-84ac-5d136d1cda8c.description=
Enumerates subkeys that live under a specific registry key.

Inputs\:
host - hostname or ip address
key - The key to create. For Example\: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Services\Browser
username - user to connect to host as
password - password to connect to host as

Responses\:
success - registry key values were enumerated
failure - something went wrong

Returns\:
The raw XML response.

Extra Results\:
subKeys - a Comma delimited list of the keys that are children of this key.
800400aa-4853-4805-9b7e-8e1cb533d7a9.dea50291-aa9c-4433-aca1-f5e7e4ec2b0b.prompt=Enter a value for host 800400aa-4853-4805-9b7e-8e1cb533d7a9.description=
This sample demonstrates how to manipulate the Windows Registry.

Inputs\:
host - the host to manipulate the registry on during the sample.
username - an administrator user on host.
password - password for username.
key - A test key that will be created and deleted.
valueName - The name of a value to create\delete
value - the first value that will be set to valueName (NOTE\: it is also changed to a surprise value).

Responses\:
success - all operations completed.
failure - something went wrong.
